e of souls of which the [[headless horseman]] can never cross and stick a knife in a pumpkin proving he was there. The following night after being chased by the bully in disguise he meets the ghost of ''[[Ichabod Crane]]'' who has lost his way. After pointing him in the direction away from the bridge, Ian is soon chased by the real headless horseman. Ian manages to make it across the bridge of souls destroying the horseman, and then runs into Crane again who remarks that he meant to go \"that way\" referring to the bridge.\n*{{Italics colon|Storyteller}} '''Tucker'''\n*{{Italics colon|Guest star}} [[Arthur Holden]] as Ichabod Crane's Ghost\n*{{Italics colon|Notable cast}} [[Rachel Wilson]] as ''Katie''\n| LineColor       = 216424\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 28\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = The Tale of Apartment 214\n| DirectedBy      = [[Scott Peters (writer)|Scott Peters]]\n| WrittenBy       = Scott Peters\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1994|1|15}}\n| ShortSummary    = After Stacey moves into a new apartment with her mom, she befriends an elderly woman living next door by coming by for visits. The old woman tells Stacey to visit her on a special day of importance in particular to which Stacey promises to do so. Stacey winds up reluctantly breaking her promise which hurts and upsets the old woman who later reveals that the day in particular was her death date before she vanishes leaving the apartment vacant. Stacey later asks the apartment manager about the apartment, and he replies that he has been unable to rent it due to haunting rumors. Stacey returns to the apartment pleading for forgiveness which the old woman grants revealing that she has nowhere else to go if the apartment is rented, and is lonely. Stacey and her mom move into the old woman's apartment at a discounted price making the spirit of the elderly woman happy to no longer be alone.\n*{{Italics colon|Storyteller}} '''Kiki'''\n*The campfire was not extinguished\n| LineCol